		<h2>Benefits of SiteMesh</h2>

		<h5>Pure Java</h5>
		<p>Can be used in most Java web servers that are capable of hosting Servlet 2.3 web applications. This includes Tomcat, Jetty, Orion, Resin, WebLogic, WebSphere and <a href="usersguide/requirements.jsp">more</a>.</p>

		<h5>Free and open source</h5>
		<p>Licensed under the <a href="license.jsp">OpenSymphony Software License</a>.</p>

		<h5>Simple to learn, simple to use</h5>
		<p>You can be productive with SiteMesh in minutes, on both new and existing web sites.</p>

		<h5>Non-intrusive</h5>
		<p>SiteMesh is configured in one place. You do not need to scatter SiteMesh specific details over all the pages in your application. In fact, your content pages need not be aware of SiteMesh at all.</p>

		<h5>Tool friendly</h5>
		<p>Carry on using your favourite libraries and tools. Transparent to your existing MVC framework, page templating engine, WYSIWYG editor and content publishing system. </p>

		<h5>Minimal constraints</h5>
		<p>Web applications don't have to be rewritten to benefit from SiteMesh. </p>

		<h5>Extensible</h5>
		<p>Mechanisms for extending SiteMesh are provided for customization, where necessary. </p>

